<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1909/517299-625x325.jpg" alt="Africa's Wendy Williams fans look forward to her on air return" width="625" height="325" align="left">The 11th season of the American talk show kicked off this week in the United States with Liongate’s Debmar-Mercury announcing that Williams has been renewed for another two seasons until 2022.After the tumultuous on-again, off-again 10th season that saw Williams take several extended breaks since January 2019, dealing with health issues and chronic disease complications and a divorce from her husband Kevin Hunter, who was also axed as executive producer after eight years, the new season is still on track. “I’m so excited to launch our 11th year by letting the world know I will continue to do what I love to do so much – and for a very long time,” Williams said. She also added that the talk show “will never stop working very hard to bring our dedicated Wendy Watchers and audience ‘co-hosts’ the freshest national daytime television.”Source: NexTVAfrica.com.